A query is SIMPLE if it has a single clear intent and can be fully answered by ONE expert.
A query is COMPLEX if it combines multiple topics, requires information from multiple intents, or asks compound questions that need different expertise.

For complex queries, break them into independent sub-queries where each sub-query is answerable by a single intent.
